A teacher is in critical condition after being shot in the head at a Durban school. On Tuesday morning, paramedics responded to the scene of a shooting incident at a school in the Newlands West area of Durban. The school is believed to be Riverdene Secondary High School. “On arrival on scene a male believed to be approximately thirty years of age was found lying on the roadway next to a vehicle,” said Kyle van Reenen, Emer-G-Med spokesperson. “Closer inspection found the man to have sustained a single gunshot wound to the head and he was in a critical condition.” Van Reenen said paramedics stabilised the man before transporting him to a nearby hospital for further care. The circumstances around the shooting are still unclear at this stage but police are on scene and will be investigating further. This is a developing story.